** '''Player:''' How do I make peace with Etceteria?
** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' You should go talk to Queen Sigrid of Etceteria.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|cond=If the player is earning Prince Brand's approval:|How am I supposed to gain the trust of the Prince?}}
** '''Player:''' How am I supposed to gain the trust of the Prince?
** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' I think you may find that talking to him would be a good way to start.
** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' A ring may be an appropriate gift to formalise your friendship{{sic|No period}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|cond=If the player is earning Princess Astrid's approval:|How am I supposed to gain the trust of the Princess?}}
** '''Player:''' How am I supposed to gain the trust of the Princess?
** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' I think you may find that talking to her would be a good way to start.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Is there anything else you can tell me?}}
** '''Player:''' Is there anything else you can tell me?
** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' What would you like to know, [Sir/Madam/ {{sic}}]?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What can you tell me about the King?}}
*** '''Player:''' What can you tell me about the King?
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' King Vargas was once a brave and noble adventurer, well-loved by his subjects. Unfortunately, he was cursed while seeking a quest in the icelands to the north, and is now unable to reign.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|What can you tell me about the Prince?}}
*** '''Player:''' What can you tell me about the Prince?
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Prince Brand has always dreamed of becoming a famous bard; unfortunately, his musical and literary skills are somewhat lacking.
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' He has no interest in ruling the kingdom, and seems to spend his time daydreaming or composing quite awful poems, and sagas of totally mundane events.
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' He is rather vain, if you'll pardon my saying so; he will greatly appreciate any compliments on his poetry. He also has quite a sweet tooth.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|What can you tell me about the Princess?}}
*** '''Player:''' What can you tell me about the Princess?
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Princess Astrid thinks she'd be perfectly capable of ruling the kingdom, but her father doesn't trust her enough by herself.
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Especially since she devotes herself to the - as the King sees it - cowardly skill of archery rather than the noble skill of melee combat...
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' She is fond of jewellery, and of course she collects bows. She is also quite the conversationalist.
*** {{tcond|If the player has not gained the trust of Princess Astrid:}}
**** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Many have tried to capture her attention, but she has yet to be impressed by any of them.
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{tcond|If the player has gained the trust of Princess Astrid:}}
**** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Many have tried to capture her attention, but you are the first to succeed.
**** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|What can you tell me about Queen Sigrid?}}
*** '''Player:''' What can you tell me about Queen Sigrid?
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' Queen Sigrid is quite envious of King Vargas, since he has the larger kingdom.
*** '''Advisor Ghrim:''' The King and she have never seen eye-to-eye, but I think if you approach her you may find her quite reasonable.
*** {{tact|end}}

